What you need to know:

The controversial decision to relocate the marathon and race-walking events was made in November 2019, before the Games were postponed by a year due to the coronavirusThe Tokyo Olympics are now due to open in July 2021, and officials are insisting they will go ahead even if the pandemic is not under controlThe marathon will have three laps -- the first much longer, crossing the Toyohira River, while the second and third laps repeat a section of the first